                            <comment id="481736" author="adilger" created="Thu, 18 Dec 2025 08:50:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In addition to setting the default &lt;tt&gt;mdd_append_stripe_count = 0&lt;/tt&gt; at startup, the Lustre Manual should be updated to fix the description added in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/49725&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/49725&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-512&quot; title=&quot;The Lustre Operations Manual does not document the append_pool or append_stripe_count options&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-512&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-512&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; manual: add append_pool and append_stripe_count&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) to describe the new behavior.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One complication in the implementation is that &lt;tt&gt;mdd_object_make_hint()&lt;/tt&gt; that sets &lt;tt&gt;dah_append_stripe_count = mdd_append_stripe_count&lt;/tt&gt; does not currently have access to the client import in order to check for &lt;tt&gt;OBD_CONNECT2_NO_APPEND&lt;/tt&gt;, so this flag/state would need to be passed in to this function some way.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternately, we might consider to set/pass a new &lt;tt&gt;MDS_OPEN_NO_APPEND&lt;/tt&gt; flag, either from the client or from the MDS, so that it is available to &lt;tt&gt;mdd_object_make_hint()&lt;/tt&gt; when needed.  Note that this would only avoid the use of the plain append layout, and not affect the &lt;tt&gt;MDS_OPEN_APPEND&lt;/tt&gt; flag on the file.  If an old MDS ignores an unknown &lt;tt&gt;MDS_OPEN_NO_APPEND&lt;/tt&gt; flag, it would be possible to avoid the &lt;tt&gt;OBD_CONNECT2_NO_APPEND&lt;/tt&gt; flag entirely.  Only new clients that have (at least) the &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12738&quot; title=&quot;PFL: append of PFL file should not instantiate full layout&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12738&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12738&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch would send this flag, &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
